					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">Oh nice, much cleaner than my hack.<br /><br />I've been working towards a sp65c02 test and I'm surprised at how compatible this will be. The four main status flags are even in the same bit positions on the saved status on the stack: NV-- --ZC.<br /><br />I think RTS is the only notable problem that will have to be accepted. It doesn't increment the return address by one, so code using it for indirect jumping will fail. RTI however works the same, so that (IMO superior) approach to indirect jump can be shared without change.<br /><br />I've made PLA, PLX, and PLY set the status flags properly, by adding an INC+DEC after. Minor cost for compatibility. I might add an option to disable these.</div>

					<br clear="all" /><br />

