						<div class="postbody"><div class="quotetitle">blargg wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">I think RTS is the only notable problem that will have to be accepted. It doesn't increment the return address by one, so code using it for indirect jumping will fail. RTI however works the same, so that (IMO superior) approach to indirect jump can be shared without change.</div><br />That or a new macro <tt style="margin-left: 2px; margin-right: 2px; padding:3px; background-color: #3355aa; color: white;">rtsaddr</tt> that acts like <tt style="margin-left: 2px; margin-right: 2px; padding:3px; background-color: #3355aa; color: white;">.addr</tt> but subtracts one on platforms where needed.</div>

